#Text=Civil unrest in Iranian cities after Ahmadinejad declares victory
#Text=Sunday , June 14 , 2009
#Text=A riot in Teheran following the 2009 presidential election .
#Text=Image : shahram sharif .
#Text=Protests , riots and violence broke out in several cities in Iran on Saturday night following an election which many in Iran and the world say was fraudulent .
#Text=Demonstrations took place late into the night , with waves of police fighting protestors in Tehran , Shiraz , Mashad and Rasht .
#Text=Protesters chanting " Death to the dictator ! " occupied major streets around Tehran , with roadblocks being set up against police .
#Text=Tear gas has been deployed against protestors in the upscale Valiasr Street district of Tehran as well as at the University of Tehran .
#Text=Mir-Hossein Mousavi ( right ) at an electoral event in Zanjan
#Text=Image : Mardetanha .
#Text=The protestors are supporters of Mir-Hossein Mousavi , a candidate in the Iranian presidential election .

#Text=Mousavi accuses the Iranian government of " appalling " fraud after it reported that the nation 's current president Mahmoud Ahmadinejad , who had been expected to receive less than 50 % of the vote and have to face Mousavi in a runoff election , received 62 % .

#Text=Addressing officials in an open letter , Mousavi said , " this country has been through a grand Islamic revolution and the least message of this revolution is that our nation is alert and will oppose anyone who aims to seize the power against the law . "
#Text=The protesters , reports say , do not seek to overthrow the Islamic regime , which has been in place in Iran since 1979 , but instead to reform it .

#Text=In a second letter , Mousavi reported that he has asked Iran 's Guardian Council to nullify the electoral result and urged his supporters to wear green , take up the slogan " Allahu akbar " ( " God is great " ) and peacefully protest the official position .

#Text=In response , Ahmadinejad celebrated victory in Tehran this afternoon with his supporters , and addressing a largely-sympathetic group of reporters at a press conference , asserted that the election had been free and fair and said
#Text=The situation in the country is in a very good condition .
#Text=Iran is the most stable country in the world , and there 's the rule of law in this country , and all the people are equal before the law .
#Text=It has been reported that the safety of Ahmadinejad 's rivals could not be guaranteed .
#Text=As a result , many prominent reformists and leaders of the Islamic Iran Participation Front have been arrested .
#Text=Rumors which spread around the nation saying Mousavi himself had been detained are , however , untrue and the candidate plans to address his supporters later today .
#Text=However , the brother of former Iranian president and reformist Mohammad Khateimi has been detained .
#Text=Former president Hashemi Rafsanjani has resigned from all his posts in the government in protest .

#Text=125 members of faculty resigned in protest at Sharif University , students and faculty protesting together at the urban Tehran campus , and according to eyewitnesses , police , around 23:00 UTC , raided Teheran University , and arrested over 100 students .
#Text=Reporters Without Borders has said that the Iranian government has instituted mass censorship , with foreign journalists being asked to leave the country .
#Text=It also says an interpreter working with an Italian news crew was beaten by police .
#Text=Mobile phone services have apparently been cut , and many reformist and social networking websites have been blocked .

#Text=The Iranian government has also made use of the Internet by circulating a false invitation to a rally outside Mousavi 's headquarters ; the city square containing the headquarters has been surrounded by police , trapping thousands of Mousavi 's supporters inside .

#Text=Iranians living abroad as well as supporters of what is being called the " green revolution " , from the colors of Mousavi 's campaign , have staged demonstrations outside Iranian embassies and consulates in Rome , Kuala Lumpur , Paris , Berlin , London , and The Hague , with events planned in the United States in Chicago , Illinois and Los Angeles , California for later in the day .
#Text=Meanwhile , the U.S. does not accept the results of the Iranian election .
#Text=U.S. Secretary of State Hillary Clinton said that she hopes " genuine will and desire " of the people will reflect the results of the election .
